added.title: Hot Salad Water
added.description: When drinking tea turns the other Titans English, it's up to Robin to save America from another British invasion.

added.title: Operation Tin Man
added.description: Gizmo convinces the Titans he's kidnapped Cyborg, when in reality Cyborg's just hanging out in the HIVE tower with his girl Jinx. When Gizmo gets annoyed by Cyborg's constant presence, the two start a prank war.

added.title: Real Magic
added.description: Robin dabbles with magic, ignoring Raven's warning that he will anger the magic god.

added.title: What's the Big Idea?
added.description: Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus try to help Uncle Grandpa get an idea.

added.title: Uncle Melvins
added.description: Legendary rock band, the Melvins, team up with Uncle Grandpa to help a young girl who wants to win her school's talent show.

added.title: Back to the Library
added.description: Uncle Grandpa uses time travel to convince his past self to return a library book on time.

added.title: Our Brand is Chaos
added.description: Bubbles and Buttercup make a deal without realizing the consequences.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Land
added.description: Pizza Steve must find a way to sneak onto his own roller coaster at the newly opened Uncle Grandpa Land.

added.title: Ultimate Weapon
added.description: When Max finds out that part of an alien weapon has been unearthed in Texas, he becomes obsessed with finding it. In doing so, he leads Ben and Gwen on a wild adventure.

added.title: They Lurk Below
added.description: Max's old friend has built the world's only underwater resort, and Ben, Gwen and Max are invited for a sneak peak. But it turns out in order to power the resort, Max's friend took an energy orb from a race of underwater aliens. Now, the aliens want their energy orb back and destroy the resort in order to get it.

added.title: Dr. Animo and the Mutant Ray
added.description: Dr. Animo has broken out of jail, and has been tracking down Ben, intent on revenge. At the same time, Ben's broken off a piece of the Omnitrix, and as a result, has turned into weird alien combinations, i.e. StinkArms.

added.title: Let's Team Up Because We Aren't Bad Friends
added.description: The Warriors fear that they've been ignoring their pals, so they team up with Witchy Simone and Noville for a BIG MISSION, only to discover that their friends aren't into it anymore.

added.title: Blue Ribbon Blues
added.description: When a famous scientist comes to the school, Blossom will stop at nothing to impress him at the Science Fair even if that means putting Townsville in danger!

added.title: Little Sword of Horrors
added.description: Prohyas grows a new Magisword from a tiny seed, but doesn't know that his Carnivorous Plant Magisword is a menace to Lyvsherian society until its too late!

added.title: Once Upon a Townsville
added.description: When a dainty princess on a mission comes to Townsville, the girls must learn the superhero way isn't always the right way.

added.title: Big in Japan
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and the gang help a kid make a giant monster movie, they cast Mr. Gus as the monster.  But things get tense on the set when Mr. Gus wants to flex his acting muscles while Uncle Grandpa only wants him to flex his monster muscles.

added.title: Fashion Forward
added.description: When the Fashionistas launch a new line of brainwashing clothing, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop the fashion trend before it's too late.

added.title: The Big Sleep
added.description: When the Professor's latest invention wreaks havoc in the house, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop it before it escapes.

added.title: Evil's Encore
added.description: Dr. Animo reminisces about when he once took control of the Plumber's HQ in Mount Rushmore. (Flashback episode.)

added.title: Food Around the Corner
added.description: Ben as Gravattack attempts to moderate a fragile peace treaty, but must endure the attacks of tiny alien fleas, which have inhabited his body.

added.title: O Mother, Where Art Thou?
added.description: Ma Vreedle threatens to blow up the sun if Ben and the Plumbers don't find her missing son!

added.title: Mud Is Thicker Than Water
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Cousin Lucy try to find out how Psyphon's thugs are getting Plumber technology.

added.title: A Fistful of Brains
added.description: Grandpa Max and Rook are looking all over the galaxy for Ben, who is trapped on Khyber's hidden personal hunting preserve.

added.title: Porcentaje de Cerebro
added.description: Chico Bestia comienza a usar más del 10% de su cerebro en un esfuerzo por encontrar las imágenes ocultas en un rompecabezas.

removed.title: Brain Percentages
removed.description: Beast Boy starts using more than 10% of his brain in an effort to find the hidden images in a puzzle.

removed.title: Uncle Jokes
removed.description: BB and Cyborg invite Starfire to join in their fun as long as she avoids dreaded uncle jokes.

removed.title: Beast Man
removed.description: Beast Boy discovers he can transform into an adult man.

removed.title: Total Eclipse of the Kart
removed.description: The Powerpuff Girls compete in a race against some of their most vicious villains to win whatever is in the Mayor's mysterious box of mystery.

removed.title: Super Sweet 6
removed.description: Morbucks throws the biggest birthday party of all time, and Blossom is the only one not invited.

removed.title: 15 Minutes of Fame
removed.description: When Bubbles' video goes viral, she goes to great lengths to maintain her status as a big-time director.

removed.title: Mojo the Great
removed.description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

removed.title: Bubbles of the Opera
removed.description: When Bubbles gets a bad school photo, it sends her into an existential tailspin of darkness.
